Cody slid forward, trying to look every direction at once. The room appeared vacant but for the staircase and a small pile of
arrows resting on the ground nearby. As Cody was about to step into the room, Lulu materialized from the shadows behind him.
Cody caught the motion out of the corner of his eye and shied away with a small yelp, then relaxed, heart pounding. "Still
right on my heels, I see," he murmured, equal parts grateful and uneasy.
